When doing a debug build:

{color:#000000}cmake .. -DARROW_PARQUET=ON -DARROW_WITH_LZ4=ON -DARROW_WITH_ZLIB=ON -DC{color}
MAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -DARROW_BUILD_TESTS=ON -DARROW_COMPUTE=ON


the following tests fail:

{color:#000000}        {color}{color:#b21818} 28 - arrow-ipc-read-write-test (Failed){color} 
        {color:#b21818} 31 - parquet-internals-test (Failed){color} 
        {color:#b21818} 32 - parquet-reader-test (Failed){color} 
        {color:#b21818} 34 - parquet-arrow-test (Failed){color}

These tests also fail on Cent OS 8 on commit {color:#b26818}8d2cda61427af350a1ff7e6abdd07515a5ed094d{color}
 Maybe am setting some environment variables incorrectly?

Any reason you still need to use release 3.0.0 of Arrow?

The master branch still has the wrong GitHub link [https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/cpp/cmake_modules/ThirdpartyToolchain.cmake#L405]

We currently support Arrow 3.0.0. We have not tested with newer versions.

You can disable tests and see if the build succeeds.

I was able to workaround this by commenting out line

{code:java}
"https://github.com/boostorg/boost/archive/boost-${ARROW_BOOST_BUILD_VERSION}.tar.gz"{code}
and then the next URL was used

{code:java}
"https://github.com/ursa-labs/thirdparty/releases/download/latest/boost_${ARROW_BOOST_BUILD_VERSION_UNDERSCORES}.tar.gz"{code}

the build succeeded this way.
